definition: Hypotonia-Cystinuria syndrome (HCS) is a rare syndrome including neonatal and infantile hypotonia and failure to thrive, cystinuria type 1 and nephrolithiasis, growth retardation due to growth hormone deficiency, and minor facial dysmorphism. HCS has been described in 14 families to date. The syndrome is caused by homozygous deletion of two contiguous genes on chromosome 2: SLC3A1 and PREP (2p21).
